<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310957>
    dc:description "FIGURES 101–106. Macrohydnobius matthewsii. 101. Right antenna, dorsal view. 102. Mandibles, dorsal view. 103. Male right protibia. 104. Aedeagus, dorsal view. 105. Female sternite 8, ventral view. 106. Female coxites and styli, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 106), 0.5 mm (Figs. 104, 105), 0.75 mm (Figs. 101, 102), 1.0 mm (Fig. 103)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5310957/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310959>
    dc:description "FIGURE 107. Known North American localities of Macrohydnobius matthewsii (black dots) and M. tibiocalcaris (open square)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5310959/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

